addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a field containing the roots of unity <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mu _{n}]]></fr:tex>, of characteristic not dividing <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, i.e. <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {char}}\nolimits (\mathbb {F})\nmid  n]]></fr:tex>. If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is a cyclic Galois extension, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  = \mathbb {F}(\sqrt [n]{a})]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
